defaultWhat are the relative merits of using gas to directly provide space heating compared to centralised electricity production plus domestic heat pumps?
default&#xa0;
default 
defaultThis depends on the efficiency of the power station in c
defaultonverting gas to electricity (normally around 50%) and the Co-efficient of Performance 
default(CoP) 
defaultof the 
defaultground source
default heat pumps (normally around 400%). If heat pumps 
defaultare poorly installed there is a danger that the CoP could fall to 200% and, at that level, there would be no merit in using heat pumps. 
defaultGround source heat pumps can now be used in conjunction with solar thermal collection in summer and heat storage in gro
defaultund arrays to yield COPs of over 500%. In these installations a clear advantage can be demonstrated for centralised electricity production plus domestic 
defaultground source 
defaultheat pumps.
defaultGround source heat pumps in well insulated buildings can be set to provide ba
defaultckground heating at night (when electricity supply is significantly cheaper).
