defaultWhy is community heating/CHP not more common in the UK?
defaultLegal problems and custom have held back district heating schemes in the UK, as well as issues of measuring heat used b
defaulty customers of district heating. CHP has advantages in the heating season – but only marginal advantage in summer, unless connected to Seasonal Thermal Energy Storage.
