defaultWhat is government policy doing to promote thermal storage, and should it do more/different?
defaultWe are not yet aware of any government policy to promote thermal storage – in spite of the power of thermal storage to reduce overall energy consumption and reduce greenhouse gas emissions significantly. 
defaultGovernment policy urgently needs to recognise and p
defaultromote 
defaultSeasonal Thermal Energy Storagedefault as a means of saving carbon emissions. The Government should also encourage all forms of Heat Recovery 
defaultwhere this can be used in conjunction with thermal storage in order to save carbon emissions. 
